    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/1103</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2661. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1207. Embassy’s 1588, September 3, your 1359. We approve of the plan set
                    forth in your cablegram for the joint certification by British and American
                    consuls in South American ports of departure of the manifests of vessels which
                    proceed from South American ports to Scandinavia and Holland. When the plan
                    shall have been made definitive and the British will have decided to instruct
                    British consuls in South America, cable us in order that we [may] issue the
                    necessary instructions to American consuls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
